# Zalan, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Zalan () is a rural locality (an ulus) in Selenginsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 74 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Zalan is located 54&nbsp;km southeast of Gusinoozyorsk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Zurgan-Debe is the nearest rural locality.
